So much for the recension of Juvenal's text where the MSS differ: now for its explanation or emendation where they agree. Here also there is much to do3 more than one might fancy, considering how many readers these Satires have found and how long and often they have been edited. But the fact is that Juvenal has never been taken in hand by a critic of the first order.
